<item>
            <title>[OAK-313] Trailing slash not removed for simple path in JCR to Oak path conversion</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-313</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While converting from JCR path to Oak path the trailing slashes are not removed for simple paths. They are removed for complex path&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;assertEquals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/oak-foo:bar/oak-quu:qux&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,npMapper.getOakPath(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/foo:bar/quu:qux/&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
assertEquals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/a/b/c&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,npMapper.getOakPath(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/a/b/c/&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Of the two cases above the first one passes while the second one fails&lt;/p&gt;</description>
